      "searchable": true,
      "value": "Title taken from caption. Soldier in military issue hat panning for gold at Girdwood, Alaska. Also from caption: \"Girdwood was an old gold mining area south of Anchorage several hours by rail. We took several excursions with USO. I mention it in some of my letters. We took many pictures and I have several kodachromes, too. The water color by Charlie Keck was of an old cabin at Girdwood.\" ca. 1945. Original photograph size: 4\" x 5\".",
